reviews.review_text: One of the best Buckets This has one of the best "Hell In A Bucket"s that I've heard. Nice effects on Weir's voice that add rather than detract. I guess this was also an FM broadcast so there are nice SBDs available. Nice to have Esau in the setlist too. Not many surprises, but a nice solid show. This sounds like the clearer of the audiences here, but the two audiences available are both by seasoned tapers, so they're both worth a listen.
